Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens" addressed to "Professor Dr. H. G. Evers 6101 Traisa bei Darmstadt Heideweg 2 Germany", from Julius S. Held, dated 22.07.1976

  • Essay (reprint): 'Zwei Rubensprobleme. Die Kekropstöchter' by J. S. Held, in "Zeitschrift für Kunstgeschichte", n. 39, 1976
  • Essay (reprint): 'The four Heads of a negro in Brussels and Malibu' by J. S. Held, in "Miscellanea in memoriam Paul Coremans (1908-1965)"
  • Essay (reprint): 'On the date and function of some allegorical sketches by Rubens' by J. S. Held, in "Journal of the Warburg and Courtauld Institutes", vol. XXXVIII, 1975 (2 copies)
  • Essay (reprint): 'Gravity and Art' by J. S. Held, in "Burlington Magazine", August 1976
